  "narrative": "DRIVER\nUSD leads D1 CSM at 100 but is actively fading on H4 to 44, a 56-point divergence that is the single most important signal in this brief, while CHF accelerates to H4 CSM 100 versus D1 33 and AUD surges to H4 CSM 70 versus D1 31, both flagged as critical short-term reversals inside a Risk-Off High regime driven by US 10Y yield collapsing 0.61% even as Trumpflation news runs hot. USDCHF prints D1 Neutral H4 Sell with CHF the strongest H4 currency, AUDUSD and NZDUSD both show H4 Sell signals contradicted by their own CSM acceleration, making USDCHF the cleanest expression and AUDJPY the highest-conviction cross given AUDUSD-AUDJPY correlation at 0.90.\n\nMOMENTUM\nGaining: None\nFading: None\n\nWATCH\nTrumpflation repricing in US CPI expectations hits USDCAD directly given its D1 Strong Buy H4 Buy alignment, a further CAD flush confirms upside continuation. US 10Y yield extending its 0.61% decline pressures USDJPY which holds D1 Buy H4 Buy but loses momentum on yield divergence. Copper extending above the 1.95% daily gain triggers AUDUSD buying against its current H4 Sell signal, invalidating the short setup.",
